### Variables
# Agent API uses client certificate authentication.
# The certificate is sent as: Authorization: Bearer <Base64-encoded-client-certificate>
# Generate a client cert (signed by the app's root cert), export to Base64, and set it below.
# See XiansAi.Server.Tests/README.md "Certificate Configuration" for how to generate.
# @agentBaseUrl = https://localhost:7184
@agentBaseUrl = http://localhost:5005

# Base64-encoded client certificate (use CertificateGenerator to create; export as Cert to Base64)
@clientCertBase64 = 

# Optional: tenant context (must match cert tenant unless SysAdmin). Use for tenant-scoped secrets.
@tenantId = 99xio

# Replace with id from Create response when testing Get/Update/Delete
@secretId = 699fd9525d56097919802e3a

### ============================================
### Agent API - Secret Vault (Certificate auth)
### ============================================
# Authentication: Authorization: Bearer <base64-client-certificate>
# The Bearer value is the raw Base64-encoded client certificate, not a JWT.
# X-Tenant-Id: optional; when set, must match certificate tenant (or SysAdmin can impersonate).
# Key must be unique. Scope: omit tenantId/agentId/userId/activationName to fetch only unscoped secrets.

### 1. Create Secret
# Optional: tenantId, agentId, userId, activationName, additionalData (JSON object or string).
POST {{agentBaseUrl}}/api/agent/secrets
Authorization: Bearer {{clientCertBase64}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "key": "agent-api-secret-014",
  "value": "agent-secret-value",
  "tenantId": "hello",
  "agentId": null,
  "userId": null,
  "activationName": null,
  "additionalData": { "purpose": "webhook" }
}

###

### 2. List Secrets
GET {{agentBaseUrl}}/api/agent/secrets
Authorization: Bearer {{clientCertBase64}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 3. List Secrets (filter by tenantId, agentId, and/or activationName)
GET {{agentBaseUrl}}/api/agent/secrets?tenantId={{tenantId}}&agentId=my-agent&activationName=my-activation
Authorization: Bearer {{clientCertBase64}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 4. Fetch Secret by Key (unscoped – only returns secrets with tenant_id/agent_id/user_id/activation_name all null)
GET {{agentBaseUrl}}/api/agent/secrets/fetch?key=agent-api-secret-01
Authorization: Bearer {{clientCertBase64}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 5. Fetch Secret by Key with scope (strict match: all provided params must match document)
GET {{agentBaseUrl}}/api/agent/secrets/fetch?key=agent-api-secret-01&tenantId={{tenantId}}&agentId=my-agent&userId=user-1&activationName=my-activation
Authorization: Bearer {{clientCertBase64}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 6. Get Secret by Id
GET {{agentBaseUrl}}/api/agent/secrets/{{secretId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{clientCertBase64}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 7. Update Secret
PUT {{agentBaseUrl}}/api/agent/secrets/{{secretId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{clientCertBase64}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "value": "updated-agent-secreti",
  "tenantId": null,
  "agentId": null,
  "userId": null,
  "activationName": null,
  "additionalData": { "purpose": "webhook", "updated": true }
}

###

### 8. Delete Secret
DELETE {{agentBaseUrl}}/api/agent/secrets/{{secretId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{clientCertBase64}}
Accept: application/json

###
